name: collections::btree::set::CursorMut::<'a, T, A>::next

collections::btree::map::CursorMut::<'a,.doc:
Advances the cursor to the next gap, returning the key and value of the
 element that it moved over.

 If the cursor is already at the end of the map then `None` is returned
 and the cursor is not moved.

doc:
Advances the cursor to the next gap, returning the element that it
 moved over.

 If the cursor is already at the end of the set then `None` is returned
 and the cursor is not moved.
